milestones.description: Gary Wilson and Porterfield's 102-run partnership is IRE's highest for the 1st wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 92 between Jeremy Bray and Porterfield
Kyle McCallan has become the top wicket-taker for IRE in ODIs with 37 wickets, going past Andre Botha's 35

stories.title: Wilson and Porterfield power Ireland to series triumph
stories.subTitle: Ireland v Kenya, 2nd ODI, Dublin
stories.summary: Ireland wrapped up a comfortable series win, beating Kenya by 52 runs via the Duckworth-Lewis method, after dismissing the tourists for a below-par 175 in the second ODI in Dublin
